## 📈 PART 7 — Scaling Considerations

If you had to scale Care++ to 10K+ hospitals:

### Infrastructure
- Containerize everything with Docker
- Orchestrate with Kubernetes
- Use Helm for deployment management
- Multi-region deployment for low latency

### Database
- PostgreSQL read replicas for read-heavy workloads
- Sharding by hospital ID
- Connection pooling (HikariCP, PgBouncer)
- Audit logs in separate database

### AI Service
- GPU-backed nodes for inference (NVIDIA A100s or similar)
- Model serving with NVIDIA Triton or TorchServe
- Batch inference where possible
- Model versioning and A/B testing

### Caching
- Redis for session data
- Cache frequent EHR lookups
- Cache AI inference results where appropriate

### Observability
- Prometheus + Grafana for metrics
- Loki / ELK for logs
- Jaeger for distributed tracing
- PagerDuty alerts on critical thresholds

### Security
- HIPAA / DPDP compliance
- End-to-end encryption
- VPC isolation for databases
- Secrets in HashiCorp Vault

### CI/CD
- GitHub Actions for build/test
- Automated deployment via ArgoCD
- Canary releases for AI model updates

