1. *"I built the entire AI pipeline myself"*
   → It was a team effort. Be honest.

2. *"We used RAG / LangChain / FAISS in Care++"*
   → Paper doesn't mention these. Saying it creates a contradiction.

3. *"I trained ResNet50 / BioBERT / Llama from scratch"*
   → Computationally impossible at academic scale. You used pretrained models.

4. *"Care++ is production-deployed at hospitals"*
   → It's an academic research project. Don't inflate.

5. *"I have 5 years of experience in healthcare AI"*
   → You're a fresh graduate. Don't overstate.

6. *"The model has 100% accuracy"*
   → Paper says 96.85%. Stick to the number.

7. *"We achieved this with no challenges"*
   → Every project has challenges. Have 2-3 honest ones ready.

